---
to: "slack-notification.json"
description: "Generate Slack notification message payload"
category: notifications
requires:
  - webhook_url
variables:
  webhook_url: "Slack webhook URL"
  channel: "Slack channel (default: #alerts)"
  username: "Bot username (default: AlertBot)"
  icon_emoji: "Bot icon emoji (default: :warning:)"
  message_type: "Message type (info, warning, error, success)"
  title: "Notification title"
  message: "Main message body"
  fields: "Array of field objects (title, value, short)"
  attachments: "Array of attachment objects"
  timestamp: "Event timestamp (ISO 8601)"
mode: overwrite



---






{
  "channel": "{{ channel | default("#alerts") }}",
  "username": "{{ username | default("AlertBot") }}",
  "icon_emoji": "{{ icon_emoji | default(":warning:") }}",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "text": {
        "type": "plain_text",
        "text": "{{ title | default("System Notification") }}"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "fields": [
        {
          "type": "mrkdwn",
          "text": "*Type:*\n{{ message_type | default("info") | upper }}"
        },
        {
          "type": "mrkdwn",
          "text": "*Time:*\n{{ timestamp | default(now | date("YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm:ss")) }}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "text": {
        "type": "mrkdwn",
        "text": "{{ message | default("Notification message body") }}"
      }
    }
{% if fields | length > 0 %}
    ,
    {
      "type": "section",
      "fields": [
{% for field in fields | default([]) %}
        {
          "type": "mrkdwn",
          "text": "*{{ field.title }}:*\n{{ field.value }}"
        }{% if not loop.last %},{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
      ]
    }
{% endif %}
  ]
{% if attachments | length > 0 %}
  ,
  "attachments": [
{% for attachment in attachments %}
    {
      "color": "{{ attachment.color | default("#36a64f") }}",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "section",
          "text": {
            "type": "mrkdwn",
            "text": "{{ attachment.text | default("Attachment details") }}"
          }
        }
      ]
    }{% if not loop.last %},{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
  ]
{% endif %}
}

## Signal Theory

**Signal**: `S=(linguistic, notification, inform, json, slack-payload)`
- **Mode**: linguistic
- **Genre**: notification
- **Type**: inform
- **Format**: json
- **Structure**: slack-payload

## Usage

```bash
# Generate Slack notification
unrdf template render \
  --template packages/cli/templates/notifications/slack-notification.njk \
  --webhook-url "https://hooks.slack.com/services/..." \
  --message-type "error" \
  --title "Production Alert" \
  --message "Service unavailable"

# Send notification
curl -X POST {{ webhook_url }} \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d @slack-notification.json
```

## Message Types

### Info (Blue)
```bash
--message-type "info" \
--icon-emoji ":information_source:"
```

### Warning (Yellow)
```bash
--message-type "warning" \
--icon-emoji ":warning:"
```

### Error (Red)
```bash
--message-type "error" \
--icon-emoji ":x:"
```

### Success (Green)
```bash
--message-type "success" \
--icon-emoji ":white_check_mark:"
```

## Field Examples

```json
--fields '[
  {"title": "Service", "value": "api-gateway"},
  {"title": "Status", "value": "500"},
  {"title": "Region", "value": "us-west-2"}
]'
```

## Attachment Examples

```json
--attachments '[
  {
    "color": "#danger",
    "text": "Error details",
    "fields": [
      {"title": "Error Code", "value": "ERR-5001"},
      {"title": "Stack Trace", "value": "at..." }
    ]
  }
]'
```

## Slack API Limits

- **Max attachments**: 100
- **Max fields per section**: 10
- **Max text length**: 40,000 characters
- **Rate limiting**: 1 message per second per workspace

